    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-10T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="443"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6354/352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-10T23:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 10, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 10—6:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1766. Embassy’s 1746, April 10.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Spoke to Campbell at end of International Tin Committee meeting today. He
                        tells me Committee voted (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) that it was prepared to
                        recommend renewal of agreement to interested Government subject to
                        reservations of Bolivian Government outlined in section 3 of <pb facs="0531"
                            n="519" xml:id="pg_519"/> number 1746; and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)
                        unanimously recommended liquidation of buffer stock funds amounting to about
                        2½ million sterling by repayment of money in proportion to respective
                        contributions with exception of Siam which will go to the custodian of enemy
                        property and Indochina which will probably be placed in trust.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>With regard to Bolivian reservation about Metals Reserve contract with
                        International Tin Committee, Campbell stated Committee felt that it had been
                        framed for objectives now unobtainable under circumstances and conditions
                        which have ceased to exist. Committee was therefore willing to approach
                        Embassy to ask it to take up matter with Metals Reserve.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
